if (user is logged in)
    let them buy stock, see their transaction history, or see their portfolio
    once the user is logged in, an API call is made to get the most recent stock data
    that stock data is then used when the user makes purchases in order to calculate the total cost of the stock they are buying
 if (user buys stock)
    if (they have the money and have inputed the correct symbol to buy the stock)
        let them buy stock
        update their portfolio and order history with the info of the stock they just bought
    else
        output error message
else
    have the user create a login OR login
 
